  "texts": [
    "Medical texts often follow a structured format with a similar writing style, typically including a general description of the specimen and frequent use of common technical terms.",
    "In addition, certain diseases manifest homogeneously across patients, resulting in nearly identical report descriptions within a patient group.",
    "In such cases, the few unique terms in the reports become critical in distinguishing between different diagnoses.",
    "Therefore, these two baseline comparisons provide effective reference points for measuring the overall performance of our models.",
    "Evaluating the reports generated by HistoGPT is a non-trivial task."
  ]
}